# interfaceProperty

**Instance Property**

The name of the outlet in your interface controller to which the object is bound.

## Declaration

```swift
var interfaceProperty: String { get }
```

## Discussion

The string in this property corresponds to the name of a property in one of your [doc://com.apple.watchkit/documentation/WatchKit/WKInterfaceController] subclasses. WatchKit uses this value internally to manage the connection between the interface object and the corresponding object on Apple Watch. You do not need to use this property directly.
